    "subtask_body": "Focusing on 2-opt improvements for the current tour [11,0,7,8,18,16,15,2,14,1,6,19,13,5,12,4,9,3,10,17].\n\nThe longest edge is 17\u219211 (\u224885.4). Let me try to fix this by finding a better connection.\n\nCurrent tour edges (key long ones):\n- 17\u219211: 85.4\n- 18\u219216: 45.0\n- 2\u219214: 43.0\n- 3\u219210: 34.0\n- 10\u219217: 32.1\n\n2-opt: Try reversing segment between cities to eliminate crossing edges.\n\nTry swap: remove edges (17,11) and (0,7), add (17,0) and (11,7):\n17\u21920: sqrt(66\u00b2+3\u00b2)\u224866.1, 11\u21927: sqrt(12\u00b2+27\u00b2)\u224829.5\nOld: 85.4+11.2=96.6, New: 66.1+29.5=95.6 \u2014 tiny improvement, barely worth it.\n\nTry swap: remove (17,11) and (7,8), add (17,7) and (11,8):\n17\u21927: sqrt(71\u00b2+7\u00b2)\u224871.3, 11\u21928: sqrt(3\u00b2+40\u00b2)\u224840.1\nOld: 85.4+15.8=101.2, New: 71.3+40.1=111.4 \u2014 worse.\n\nTry swap: remove (18,16) and (15,2), add (18,15) and (16,2):\n18\u219215: sqrt(39\u00b2+45\u00b2)\u224859.6, 16\u21922: sqrt(30\u00b2+12\u00b2)\u224832.3\nOld: 45.0+14.4=59.4, New: 59.6+32.3=91.9 \u2014 worse.\n\nTry swap: remove (16,15) and (2,14), add (16,2) and (15,14):\n16\u21922: 32.3, 15\u219214: sqrt(35\u00b2+10\u00b2)\u224836.4\nOld: 38.0+43.0=81.0, New: 32.3+36.4=68.7 \u2014 saves 12.3!\n\nNew tour: [11,0,7,8,18,16,2,15,14,1,6,19,13,5,12,4,9,3,10,17]\n(reversed segment [15,2] to [2,15])\n\nNow check 17\u219211 again with this tour. Still 85.4.\n\nTry another 2-opt on new tour: remove (10,17) and (3,10), try (3,17) and (10,?):\nActually try: remove (9,3) and (10,17), add (9,10) and (3,17):\n9\u219210: sqrt(42\u00b2+21\u00b2)\u224846.9, 3\u219217: sqrt(20\u00b2+28\u00b2)\u224834.4\nOld: 21.5+32.1=53.6, New: 46.9+34.4=81.3 \u2014 worse.\n\nTry: remove (4,9) and (3,10), add (4,3) and (9,10):\n4\u21923: sqrt(6\u00b2+37\u00b2)\u224837.5, 9\u219210: 46.9\nOld: 17.1+34.0=51.1, New: 37.5+46.9=84.4 \u2014 worse.\n\nTry: remove (5,12) and (4,9), add (5,4) and (12,9):\n5\u21924: sqrt(26\u00b2+12\u00b2)\u224828.6, 12\u21929: sqrt(2\u00b2+43\u00b2)\u224843.0\nOld: 29.5+17.1=46.6, New: 28.6+43.0=71.6 \u2014 worse.\n\nTry: remove (13,5) and (12,4), add (13,12) and (5,4):\n13\u219212: sqrt(35\u00b2+5\u00b2)\u224835.4, 5\u21924: 28.6\nOld: 21.0+26.0=47.0, New: 35.4+28.6=64.0 \u2014 worse.\n\nTry: remove (17,11) and (9,3), add (17,9) and (11,3) [reverse segment 3..10..17]:\n17\u21929: sqrt(28\u00b2+8\u00b2)\u224829.1, 11\u21923: sqrt(63\u00b2+8\u00b2)\u224863.5\nOld: 85.4+21.5=106.9, New: 29.1+63.5=92.6 \u2014 saves 14.3!\n\nNew tour after this 2-opt (reverse segment from 3 to 17):\n[11,0,7,8,18,16,2,15,14,1,6,19,13,5,12,4,9,17,10,3] with 11 connecting back to 3.\nWait, need to be careful. Current tour: [11,0,7,8,18,16,2,15,14,1,6,19,13,5,12,4,9,3,10,17]\nIndices: 0=11,1=0,2=7,3=8,4=18,5=16,6=2,7=15,8=14,9=1,10=6,11=19,12=13,13=5,14=12,15=4,16=9,17=3,18=10,19=17\n\nRemove edges (tour[19],tour[0])=(17,11) and (tour[16],tour[17])=(9,3).\nReverse segment tour[17..19]: [3,10,17] \u2192 [17,10,3].\nNew tour: [11,0,7,8,18,16,2,15,14,1,6,19,13,5,12,4,9,17,10,3]\nNew edges: 9\u219217: 29.1, 3\u219211: 63.5\nOld edges: 9\u21923: 21.5, 17\u219211: 85.4\nSavings: (21.5+85.4)-(29.1+63.5) = 106.9-92.6 = 14.3 \u2713\n\nNew estimated total: 519.4 - 12.3 - 14.3 = 492.8\n\nLet me verify the new tour: [11,0,7,8,18,16,2,15,14,1,6,19,13,5,12,4,9,17,10,3]\nEdges:\n11\u21920: 24.0, 0\u21927: 11.2, 7\u21928: 15.8, 8\u219218: 2.2, 18\u219216: 45.0, 16\u21922: 32.3, 2\u219215: sqrt(8\u00b2+12\u00b2)=14.4, 15\u219214: 36.4, 14\u21921: 22.6, 1\u21926: 18.2, 6\u219219: 13.0, 19\u219213: 5.4, 13\u21925: 21.0, 5\u219212: 29.5, 12\u21924: 26.0, 4\u21929: 17.1, 9\u219217: 29.1, 17\u219210: 32.1, 10\u21923: 34.0, 3\u219211: 63.5\nTotal: 24+11.2+15.8+2.2+45+32.3+14.4+36.4+22.6+18.2+13+5.4+21+29.5+26+17.1+29.1+32.1+34+63.5 = 492.8\n\nStill have 18\u219216: 45.0 as a long edge. Try to fix it.\nRemove (8,18) and (18,16): these are consecutive so can't 2-opt directly.\nTry: remove (7,8) and (18,16), add (7,18) and (8,16):\n7\u219218: sqrt(11\u00b2+14\u00b2)\u224817.8, 8\u219216: sqrt(1\u00b2+46\u00b2)\u224846.0\nOld: 15.8+45.0=60.8, New: 17.8+46.0=63.8 \u2014 worse.\n\nTry: remove (8,18) and (16,2), add (8,16) and (18,2):\n8\u219216: 46.0, 18\u21922: sqrt(31\u00b2+33\u00b2)\u224845.3\nOld: 2.2+32.3=34.5, New: 46.0+45.3=91.3 \u2014 worse.\n\nTry or-opt: move city 16 elsewhere. 16 is at (2,3), near 8(3,49) and 2(32,15).\nRemove 16 from between 18 and 2: saves 18\u219216 (45.0) + 16\u21922 (32.3) - 18\u21922 (45.3) = 32.0\nInsert 16 between 15 and 14: 15\u219216: sqrt(38\u00b2+0\u00b2)=38.0, 16\u219214: sqrt(73\u00b2+10\u00b2)\u224873.7, saves 15\u219214 (36.4) = cost 38+73.7-36.4=75.3 \u2014 net: 32.0-75.3 = -43.3, worse.\n\nInsert 16 between 2 and 15: 2\u219216: 32.3, 16\u219215: 38.0, saves 2\u219215 (14.4) = cost 32.3+38-14.4=55.9, net: 32-55.9=-23.9, worse.\n\n16 is really isolated at (2,3). Best neighbors: 15(40,3)=38, 2(32,15)=32.3, 18(1,48)=45.\n\nTry: remove (18,16) and (16,2), insert 16 between 15 and 14:\nSaves: 45+32.3=77.3, adds: 18\u21922=45.3, 15\u219216=38, 16\u219214=73.7, removes 15\u219214=36.4\nNet change: (45.3+38+73.7-36.4) - 77.3 = 120.6-77.3 = +43.3 \u2014 worse.\n\n16 seems stuck. Let me try a different approach for the 18\u219216 edge.\nWhat if we route: ...8\u219218\u219216\u219215\u21922... but reorder to ...8\u219216\u219218\u2192... No, 18 is at (1,48) and 16 at (2,3), so 18\u219216=45 is unavoidable if they're adjacent.\n\nActually, what if 16 connects to 15 directly and 18 connects elsewhere?\nTour segment: ...7\u21928\u219218\u2192...\u219216\u219215\u21922...\nTry: ...7\u21928\u219218\u219211\u2192...\u219216\u219215\u21922... but 11 is already used at start.\n\nLet me try or-opt: move 18 to be adjacent to 8 and 7 differently.\nCurrent: 7\u21928\u219218\u219216. 18 at (1,48) is very close to 8(3,49). \nWhat if: ...11\u219218\u21928\u21927\u21920\u2192... (reverse the left side)?\n11\u219218: sqrt(1\u00b2+41\u00b2)\u224841.0